        Adds a prefix to the subject, when it is displayed in error messages. This is especially useful in the context of types that have no helpful toString() representation, e.g. boolean. Writing assertThat(foo).named("foo").isTrue(); then results in a more reasonable error message.

        named() takes a format template and argument objects which will be substituted into the template, similar to String.format(String, Object...), the chief difference being that extra parameters (for which there are no template variables) will be appended to the resulting string in brackets. Additionally, this only supports the %s template variable type.
